<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1675,2037]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Male imago. General coloration faint in the old pinned 
<typeStatus box="[899,965,1750,1776]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">types</typeStatus>
. Genitalia: long and cylindrical penes completely separated from their bases (
<figureCitation box="[618,707,1787,1813]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 43" captionStartId="16.[151,273,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[221,1357,197,1936]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[221,1366,194,1957]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 43. Tortopsis unguiculatus, type male genitalia, photographs and interpretations (line drawings). 41, ventral view; 42, lateral view; 43, laterodorsal view (details of apex of penes)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195438/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[674,707,1787,1813]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="41.0">41</number>
</figureCitation>
); sclerotized spine on inner apical margin with wide rounded base and slightly hooked apex (
<figureCitation box="[524,612,1824,1850]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 43" captionStartId="16.[151,273,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[221,1357,197,1936]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[221,1366,194,1957]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 43. Tortopsis unguiculatus, type male genitalia, photographs and interpretations (line drawings). 41, ventral view; 42, lateral view; 43, laterodorsal view (details of apex of penes)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195438/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[579,612,1824,1850]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="43.0">43</number>
</figureCitation>
); parastyli long and acute, markedly curved dorsally, the main axis of the basal third, form a 
<number box="[427,459,1862,1888]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="90.0">90</number>
° angle with the axis of the distal third (
<figureCitation box="[941,1032,1862,1888]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 43" captionStartId="16.[151,273,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[221,1357,197,1936]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[221,1366,194,1957]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 43. Tortopsis unguiculatus, type male genitalia, photographs and interpretations (line drawings). 41, ventral view; 42, lateral view; 43, laterodorsal view (details of apex of penes)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195438/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[998,1032,1862,1888]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
); parastyli conical and entire, not furrowed longitudinally (
<figureCitation box="[446,534,1899,1925]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 43" captionStartId="16.[151,273,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[221,1357,197,1936]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[221,1366,194,1957]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 43. Tortopsis unguiculatus, type male genitalia, photographs and interpretations (line drawings). 41, ventral view; 42, lateral view; 43, laterodorsal view (details of apex of penes)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195438/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[501,534,1899,1925]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="41.0">41</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1675,2037]" lastBlockId="23.[151,1437,152,327]" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="24" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Discussion and diagnosis. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ulmer" box="[513,674,1936,1962]" pageId="22" pageNumber="35" refString="Ulmer, G. (1920) Neue Ephemeropteren. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 85 (A), 1 - 80." type="journal article" year="1920">
Ulmer (
<number box="[605,666,1936,1962]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1920.0">1920</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described this species from 
<specimenCount box="[1014,1094,1936,1962]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="male">
<number box="[1014,1029,1936,1962]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="3.0">3</number>
male
</specimenCount>
imagos from 
<collectingCountry box="[1262,1381,1936,1962]" name="Colombia" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, and later (
<bibRefCitation author="Ulmer" box="[221,376,1974,2000]" pageId="22" pageNumber="35" refString="Ulmer, G. (1942) Alte und neue Eintagsfliegen (Ephemeropteren) aus Sud- und Mittelamerika. Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung, 103, 98 - 128." type="journal article" year="1942">
Ulmer, 
<number box="[314,376,1974,2000]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1942.0">1942</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) provided a description of a female imago from 
<collectingCountry box="[967,1085,1974,2000]" name="Colombia" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and cited some male imagos from Reventazón (
<collectingCountry box="[373,511,2011,2037]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
). Additional records exist for this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[1047,1141,2011,2037]" name="Mexico" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1154,1276,2011,2037]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
(Zelaya) and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,283,152,178]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Maes" box="[299,435,152,178]" pageId="23" pageNumber="34" refString="Maes, J. M. (1988) Catalogo de los Ephemeroptera y Plecoptera de Nicaragua. Revista Nicaraguense de Entomologia, 2, 49 - 50." type="journal article" year="1988">
Maés 
<number box="[374,435,152,178]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="1988.0">1988</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[504,634,152,178]" name="Guatemala" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[694,811,152,178]" name="Honduras" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Honduras</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lugo-Ortiz" box="[828,1217,152,178]" pageId="23" pageNumber="34" refString="Lugo-Ortiz, C. R. &amp; McCafferty W. P. (1996) Central American Tortopus (Ephemeroptera: Polymitarcyidae): a unique new species and new country records. Entomological News, 107, 23 - 27." type="journal article" year="1996">
Lugo-Ortiz &amp; McCafferty 
<number box="[1153,1217,152,178]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), but this material should be revised with the new data offered here to confirm its specific identity. 
<taxonomicName box="[1087,1354,189,214]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Tortopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unguiculatus">
<emphasis box="[1087,1354,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Tortopsis unguiculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from all other species of the genus by: 
<number box="[775,788,226,252]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="1.0">1</number>
) fore wing length 9.0–11.0 mm (male), 11.0–12.0 mm (female); 
<number box="[268,284,264,290]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="2.0">2</number>
) wings hyaline translucent, veins whitish translucent; 
<number box="[934,949,264,290]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="3.0">3</number>
) parastyli long and very strongly curved (
<figureCitation box="[159,247,301,327]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 43" captionStartId="16.[151,273,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[221,1357,197,1936]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[221,1366,194,1957]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 43. Tortopsis unguiculatus, type male genitalia, photographs and interpretations (line drawings). 41, ventral view; 42, lateral view; 43, laterodorsal view (details of apex of penes)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195438/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
Fig. 
<number box="[214,247,301,327]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
); 
<number box="[269,285,301,327]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="4.0">4</number>
) penes cylindrical, apical spine with wide base and a small hook (
<figureCitation box="[1059,1147,301,327]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 43" captionStartId="16.[151,273,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[221,1357,197,1936]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[221,1366,194,1957]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 43. Tortopsis unguiculatus, type male genitalia, photographs and interpretations (line drawings). 41, ventral view; 42, lateral view; 43, laterodorsal view (details of apex of penes)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195438/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
Fig. 
<number box="[1114,1147,301,327]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="43.0">43</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
